# document models must be added to the vetra drive by default

After creating a document model via `createDocument`, it must be added to the vetra drive using `addActions` with an `ADD_FILE` action:

```typescript
addActions({
  documentId: "vetra-{hash}",  // the vetra drive ID
  actions: [{
    type: "ADD_FILE",
    scope: "global",
    input: { id: documentId, ... }
  }]
});
```

Since [[vetra drive holds source documents while preview drive holds instances]], document models (source/definition documents) always go to the vetra drive. Only actual document instances go to the preview drive.

